  <div class="section-head" style="margin-top:34px;"><div><div class="kicker">Weekly owner actions</div><h2 class="section-title">The operating rhythm</h2></div><p class="section-note">Reporting cannot be a vibe. Each week has a meeting rhythm, required inputs and consequences.</p></div>

  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card gold"><div class="label">Monday</div><h3>Commercial war room</h3><p>Oli reports paid-ticket pace, source mix, phase performance, discount usage, bulk orders, abandoned checkout and average realised price. Will reports Closed Won, weighted pipeline, stuck deals, next actions, sponsor concentration risk and exceptions. HPL reports spend, CTR, CPL, purchase starts, purchases, report downloads, sponsor enquiries and buyer quality. Rory’s team reports free operator-ticket progress, named operator targets and sensitive relationship issues. Desi reports blockers, dependencies and delivery risks.</p></div>
    <div class="card blue"><div class="label">Wednesday</div><h3>Sales, marketing and content sync</h3><p>Oli shares lead quality, buyer objections and ticket conversion friction. Will shares sponsor objections, proposal feedback and account gaps. Kim and Media share editorial assets, report progress, newsletter performance and podcast opportunities. Rory shares speaker proof, operator-safe content angles and approval risks. Alina shares community signals, named account signals, influencer targets and competitor sightings. HPL shares creative learnings and what gets scaled or killed.</p></div>
    <div class="card green"><div class="label">Friday</div><h3>Owner action check</h3><p>Each owner answers four questions: what shipped, what failed, what changes next week, and what needs escalation before Monday? No verbal-only updates. No hidden blockers. No “on track” without numbers.</p></div>
